03:02.680 --> 03:04.989
MALE NARRATOR:
<i>The place: New York City.</i>

03:05.160 --> 03:09.073
<i>The time: Now. 1962.</i>

03:09.240 --> 03:11.913
<i>And there's no time or place like it.</i>

03:12.080 --> 03:16.870
<i>If you've got a dream, this is the place</i>
<i>to make that dream come true.</i>

03:17.440 --> 03:21.228
<i>That's why the soaring population</i>
<i>of hopeful dreamers has just reached...</i>

03:21.400 --> 03:24.198
<i>... eight million people.</i>

03:24.360 --> 03:28.592
<i>Oh, make that eight million and one.</i>

03:28.760 --> 03:32.150
WOMAN 1: Hey, taxi! Taxi! Taxi!
WOMAN 2: Taxi!

03:32.320 --> 03:34.038
Wait. Where are you going?

03:48.360 --> 03:49.588
Down with the bomb.

03:49.760 --> 03:52.718
PROTESTERS: <i>Down with the bomb.</i>
<i>Down with the bomb.</i>

03:52.880 --> 03:56.236
<i>Down with the bomb.</i>
<i>Down with the bomb.</i>

03:56.400 --> 03:57.515
<i>Down with the b...</i>

03:57.680 --> 03:59.238
[SCREAMING]

04:31.320 --> 04:32.958
[DINGING]

04:46.920 --> 04:48.273
[DINGING]

04:55.680 --> 04:58.240
Barbara?

04:58.400 --> 05:00.755
- Barbara Novak?
- Oh, I think so.

05:00.920 --> 05:03.753
- Oh, thank goodness you're here.
- Vikki?

05:03.920 --> 05:06.150
Vikki Hiller, your editor, in the flesh.

05:06.320 --> 05:08.834
It is so nice to finally
meet you in person.

05:09.000 --> 05:10.991
My goodness, you're gorgeous.

05:12.040 --> 05:15.157
We'll have a photo shoot for
the book jacket. There's time.

05:15.320 --> 05:18.790
The book doesn't come out for a week.
One week. Oh, my.

05:18.960 --> 05:21.394
Don't be nervous. Cigarette?

05:22.360 --> 05:23.918
[COUGHING]

05:24.080 --> 05:26.878
Barbara, this is my secretary, Gladys.
Gladys, Barbara Novak.

05:27.040 --> 05:28.917
Oh, I know. It's a pleasure.

05:29.080 --> 05:33.039
Hello, Gladys. I'm glad to finally
have a face to put with the voice.

05:33.200 --> 05:35.794
Vik, I need you to sign off
on this pronto.

05:36.840 --> 05:39.070
Maurice Johns, art director.

05:39.560 --> 05:42.597
Barbara Novak, your cover.

05:45.240 --> 05:47.754
Oh, Maurice. I love it!

05:47.920 --> 05:50.354
<i>Down With Love.</i> Hear, hear.

05:50.520 --> 05:52.431
I wish someone had
written your book...

05:52.600 --> 05:54.909
...10 years ago before
it was too late for me.

05:55.080 --> 05:56.991
Gladys, it's never too late.

05:57.160 --> 06:00.630
Great job. Sorry if the guys in
reproduction have been riding your tail.

06:00.800 --> 06:02.791
Well, I'm not.

06:05.920 --> 06:08.150
They're ready for you in the lion's den.

06:11.400 --> 06:14.949
- Lion's den?
- Oh, don't worry. You'll be fine.

06:16.400 --> 06:19.790
Just take a deep breath.

06:22.520 --> 06:24.238
[COUGHS]

06:29.520 --> 06:32.432
Gentlemen, this is Miss Novak.

06:35.560 --> 06:37.073
- E.G.
- C.B.

06:37.240 --> 06:38.832
- C.W.
- J.B.

06:39.000 --> 06:40.592
- J.R.
- R.J.

06:40.760 --> 06:43.274
- Okay.
- O.K. Can't make it. He's down with T.B.

06:43.440 --> 06:45.476
Oh, what a shame. Is it serious?

06:45.640 --> 06:49.519
No, they're just having breakfast.
T.B. Is Theodore Banner.

06:49.680 --> 06:52.877
The owner of Banner House.
The fellow publishing your book.

06:53.320 --> 06:55.834
That's his portrait, there.

06:57.880 --> 07:01.475
Sorry if we've kept you, but Barbara hit
a storm on her way down from Maine.

07:01.640 --> 07:03.631
So you've come down from Maine, huh?

07:03.800 --> 07:05.631
Well, you remember, C.B.

07:05.800 --> 07:08.268
Miss Novak is the farmer's
daughter librarian...

07:08.440 --> 07:11.796
...who spent the long, cold New England
winter writing her manuscript...

07:11.960 --> 07:14.030
...by the light of a Ionely oil lamp.

07:14.200 --> 07:16.430
C. B:
I'm at a loss here, ladies.

07:16.600 --> 07:20.354
I'm afraid I don't know exactly
what Miss Novak's book is about.

07:20.520 --> 07:24.149
Miss Novak's book is a serious work
of nonfiction entitled...

07:24.320 --> 07:26.595
Vikki, excuse me, it's right behind you.

07:26.760 --> 07:28.751
Would you mind pouring me
a cup of coffee?

07:31.320 --> 07:35.916
It's a serious work of nonfiction entitled
<i>Down With Love.</i>

07:36.080 --> 07:39.117
- This is empty.
- Lf you're making a pot, I'll have a cup.

07:39.280 --> 07:40.998
- Count me in.
C. W: Likewise.

07:41.160 --> 07:42.559
- Ditto.
- None for me, Vikki.

07:42.720 --> 07:43.948
Thanks, R.J.

07:44.120 --> 07:45.473
I'll have a Sanka.

07:48.960 --> 07:52.555
As I was saying, the central thesis of
Miss Novak's book, <i>Down With Love...</i>

07:52.720 --> 07:56.030
...is that women will never be happy
until they become independent...

07:56.200 --> 07:59.749
...as individuals by achieving
equal participation in the work force.

07:59.920 --> 08:02.673
And how do you propose
women do this, Miss Novak?

08:02.840 --> 08:06.469
By saying, "Down with love."

08:06.640 --> 08:08.312
Love is a distraction.

08:08.480 --> 08:11.836
If women stopped falling in love,
it would be the end of the human race.

08:12.000 --> 08:12.989
BARBARA:
Not at all.

08:13.160 --> 08:18.917
I say women should refrain from love,
C.W., not sex.

08:19.080 --> 08:20.798
Isn't that the same thing?

08:23.720 --> 08:25.392
I mean, for women.

08:25.560 --> 08:28.870
It won't be, after they've mastered
the three levels in my book...

08:29.040 --> 08:32.191
...that will teach any woman
to live life the way a man does.

08:32.360 --> 08:37.195
Level 1 instructs women to abstain from
men altogether so they'll stop thinking...

08:37.360 --> 08:40.909
...that the pleasures experienced
during the sex act are related to love.

08:41.080 --> 08:45.870
They're not. As women will learn by
practicing the self-pleasuring technique...

08:46.040 --> 08:49.555
...that I've detailed in chapter 7,
entitled:

08:49.920 --> 08:51.353
"Up With Chocolate."

08:51.520 --> 08:55.399
You see, gentlemen, the female
experience is a biological reaction...

08:55.560 --> 08:59.109
...to chocolate that triggers the same
pleasurable responses in the brain...

08:59.280 --> 09:00.998
...as are triggered during sex.

09:01.160 --> 09:04.470
By substituting chocolate for sex,
the female will soon learn...

09:04.640 --> 09:07.313
...the difference between sex and love.

09:07.480 --> 09:11.234
Love for a man
will no longer occupy her mind.

09:11.400 --> 09:15.359
She will now find that she has the time
and the energy to move on to Level 2...

09:15.520 --> 09:19.229
...where taking on new challenges will
lead to the self-sufficience of Level 3...

09:19.400 --> 09:23.188
...where the woman becomes active in
the workplace and earns and achieves...

09:23.360 --> 09:27.751
...an unequivocal equality with men.

09:31.480 --> 09:34.358
And all this time the woman
is abstaining from sex?

09:34.520 --> 09:35.953
Heavens, no.

09:36.120 --> 09:40.477
By Level 3, she can have sex
whenever she likes, without love...

09:40.640 --> 09:45.953
...and enjoy it the way a man does,
"à la carte."

09:48.320 --> 09:52.552
Well, Miss Novak,
your theories may have worked...

09:52.720 --> 09:55.871
...with the gentlemen up in Maine,
but the men in Manhattan...

09:56.040 --> 09:59.476
...are not the fine, upstanding,
straightforward men of Maine.

09:59.640 --> 10:03.394
The men of Manhattan are devious.
They're dangerous.

10:03.560 --> 10:05.551
They'll be coming at you
from every angle.

10:05.720 --> 10:08.314
When you're watching your front,
they'll attack the rear.

10:08.480 --> 10:11.711
And when you're protecting your rear,
they'll drop out of the sky.

10:15.880 --> 10:17.871
[BOSSA NOVA TRIPLETS
SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY]

10:19.640 --> 10:22.712
BOSSA NOVA GIRL:
One more kiss.

10:26.000 --> 10:30.676
- Easy, baby. Careful you don't fall out.
- Oh!

10:32.240 --> 10:33.229
Bye-bye.

10:41.720 --> 10:44.951
RECEPTIONIST:
Very good. I'll let him know.

10:45.120 --> 10:47.998
Mr. McMannus, Catcher Block
has just landed on the roof.

10:55.200 --> 10:57.191
[WOMEN GASPING
AND CLEARING THROATS]

10:57.360 --> 10:58.873
WOMAN:
<i>Know</i> magazine.

11:03.720 --> 11:06.234
- Are you Catcher Block's secretary?
- Yes, Mr. McMannus.

11:06.400 --> 11:08.391
I'm Sally. I'm new.

11:08.560 --> 11:12.269
They're always new. When he gets in,
tell him to see me. He's fired.

11:16.480 --> 11:17.993
- You're fired.
CATCHER: No, I'm not.

11:18.160 --> 11:19.513
Oh, yes, you are.

11:19.680 --> 11:22.592
You can take your Pulitzer
and your beloved Underwood...

11:22.760 --> 11:25.149
...and your change of underwear
and clear out.

11:25.320 --> 11:27.151
Do you work for me?

11:29.680 --> 11:32.558
You had a story due yesterday,
but I gave you more time.

11:32.720 --> 11:37.191
I held the presses so you could get
your scoop on Nazis hiding in Argentina.

11:37.360 --> 11:39.430
Then I see this.

11:40.520 --> 11:41.919
"Item:

11:42.080 --> 11:45.117
<i>Know</i> magazine's star journalist,
Catcher Block, ladies' man...

11:45.280 --> 11:49.239
...man's man, man about town,
was seen leaving the Copa last night...

11:49.400 --> 11:52.756
...with a doggy bag and three girls
from the floor show."

11:52.920 --> 11:55.229
I took the bossa nova triplets
to Cocoa Beach.

11:55.400 --> 11:56.719
NASA was throwing a luau.

11:56.880 --> 11:59.314
Oh, well, I hope you enjoyed it.

11:59.480 --> 12:02.517
Because unless you found Nazis
hiding at your luau, you're fired.

12:04.640 --> 12:08.758
There were Nazis hiding at your luau!
I knew you'd do it.

12:08.920 --> 12:10.319
What do you got for me, Catch?

12:10.480 --> 12:14.155
CATCHER: Argentina isn't the only hiding
place. They're hiding in Florida too.

12:14.320 --> 12:16.356
Wow. How? Who's hiding them?

12:16.520 --> 12:18.875
- We are.
- We... Americans?

12:19.040 --> 12:21.554
Why? Nazis are bad. We're good.

12:21.720 --> 12:24.439
Yeah, but some bad Nazis
are good scientists.

12:24.600 --> 12:28.229
Like the guy building the rocket to land
on the moon and win us the space race.

12:28.400 --> 12:31.312
He's a Nazi. And I saw
the top-secret file to prove it.

12:31.480 --> 12:35.109
- Here, I brought you a souvenir.
- Whoa!

12:37.200 --> 12:40.829
A top-secret NASA
security clearance badge.

12:41.000 --> 12:43.878
- How did you get this?
- Blame it on the bossa nova.

12:44.880 --> 12:47.633
- The triplets?
- Yeah.

12:47.800 --> 12:54.273
You see, Lo shakes her maracas
and Rosa bounces her bongos...

12:54.440 --> 12:59.639
...while Nena is all hands.
120 words a minute.

12:59.800 --> 13:02.189
The story, it's written?

13:02.360 --> 13:04.271
Whoa, Catch!

13:04.440 --> 13:06.908
But is it safe to print?
NASA is gonna blow its stack.

13:07.080 --> 13:10.959
Well, they forgave Germany,
they can forgive us.

13:11.120 --> 13:13.873
Get someone from Legal up here.

13:14.720 --> 13:17.917
Yes, sir. Yes, sir. Yes, sir.

13:18.080 --> 13:19.069
Yes, sir.

13:19.240 --> 13:22.437
My analyst says I only react
to you with such vehement loathing...

13:22.600 --> 13:24.431
...because I admire you so much.

13:24.600 --> 13:27.433
He says I resent you
for being a self-made man.

13:27.600 --> 13:29.989
As opposed to the son
of a self-made man.

13:30.160 --> 13:33.596
Here, I hope you have your garters
from last night. There's none in here.

13:33.760 --> 13:35.159
Garters?

13:35.320 --> 13:37.788
I haven't worn garters
since Nixon conceded.

13:37.960 --> 13:39.791
What are you, turning into a beatnik?

13:39.960 --> 13:43.555
Oh, step into the future, Mac,
garters are a thing of the past.

13:45.440 --> 13:47.954
I don't know, Catch.

13:48.120 --> 13:50.918
I have enough of an insecurity
complex without worrying...

13:51.080 --> 13:53.719
...about my socks falling down.

13:54.520 --> 13:58.149
How can you know you won't show
a shiny shin when you cross your legs?

13:58.320 --> 13:59.799
It's a miracle of the space age.

13:59.960 --> 14:05.114
Sock manufacturers are using new
fibers like Lycra, Orlon and Dacron...

14:05.280 --> 14:08.113
...to put super stay-up power
into their over-the-calf sock.

14:09.440 --> 14:11.476
PETER: <i>What is the average length</i>
<i>for most men?</i>

14:11.640 --> 14:12.709
CATCHER:
<i>How would I know?</i>

14:12.880 --> 14:15.553
<i>Do you think I spend time</i>
<i>in the locker room looking around...</i>

14:15.720 --> 14:18.917
<i>...making a comparative study?</i>
<i>- Let me see yours again, then.</i>

14:19.080 --> 14:23.710
<i>- We could measure. I'll get a ruler.</i>
<i>- Better make it a yardstick.</i>

14:23.880 --> 14:27.031
Let's be accurate.
Make sure you've got it fully extended.

14:27.200 --> 14:29.156
Here you have it. Up the whole way.

14:29.320 --> 14:31.914
CATCHER: <i>It stays up all the way</i>
<i>all day long, Mac.</i>

14:32.080 --> 14:35.436
<i>That's the miracle I told you about.</i>
<i>Better living through chemistry.</i>

14:35.600 --> 14:37.431
<i>You got 16 inches.</i>

14:37.600 --> 14:39.989
<i>Sixteen inches!</i>

14:40.160 --> 14:42.390
<i>How long does a man 's hose</i>
<i>have to be?</i>

14:42.560 --> 14:45.120
<i>That's 32 inches of confidence</i>
<i>in every step.</i>

14:45.280 --> 14:47.635
Don't forget, I've got two of them.

14:49.680 --> 14:51.238
[RATTLING]

14:52.360 --> 14:54.590
I don't believe it.
You went through another one.

14:54.760 --> 14:56.034
That's three this month.

14:56.200 --> 14:59.112
What is it about the workplace
that women can't seem to handle?

15:00.160 --> 15:02.469
Men. They want us to fail.

15:02.640 --> 15:04.631
Inviting me to New York
to launch my book...

15:04.800 --> 15:07.075
...when they have no intention
of promoting it.

15:07.240 --> 15:09.595
- Don't worry. I have a plan.
- You do?

15:09.760 --> 15:13.389
Remember when you called to say you'd
like publicity where men would see it?

15:13.560 --> 15:17.155
"Perhaps in a men's magazine," you said.
A prestigious men's magazine.

15:17.320 --> 15:20.756
The most widely circulated
and highly respected men's magazine.

15:20.920 --> 15:22.911
- <i>Know?</i>
- Yes, you did.

15:23.080 --> 15:25.958
No, I mean <i>Know.</i>
<i>Know</i> magazine for men in the know.

15:26.120 --> 15:27.917
Oh. Yes, exactly.

15:28.080 --> 15:30.913
- You got us advertising in <i>Know?</i>
- I did better.

15:31.080 --> 15:36.154
I got you a cover story written by <i>Know</i>
magazine's star journalist, Catcher Block.

15:36.320 --> 15:39.551
Catcher Block? The ladies' man,
man's man, man about town?

15:39.720 --> 15:43.395
Oh, Vikki, you're the best friend
a girl from Maine who wrote a book...

15:43.560 --> 15:45.676
...and came to New York
could ever have.

15:45.840 --> 15:51.153
You don't know the half of it. I hear
Catcher Block is gorgeous and eligible.

15:52.360 --> 15:54.476
Not that that matters to us.

15:54.640 --> 15:56.312
Down with love.

15:56.480 --> 15:59.631
I can't believe it.
Me on the cover of <i>Know.</i>

15:59.800 --> 16:00.915
<i>Know.</i>

16:01.080 --> 16:02.798
- No.
PETER: Catch, please, I promised.

16:02.960 --> 16:04.439
It's one cover story.

16:04.600 --> 16:08.070
A girl's never called me in my life,
let alone invited me for a drink.

16:08.240 --> 16:11.710
I think this Vikki really likes me.
I think I might really like her.

16:11.880 --> 16:13.518
I'm sure I would if she likes me.

16:13.680 --> 16:16.478
And she does, because I told her
as owner of <i>Know</i> magazine...

16:16.640 --> 16:17.914
...I had pull with my staff.

16:18.080 --> 16:21.311
Then pull your staff with one
of your other writers. I'm not doing it.

16:21.480 --> 16:23.072
No, it can't be anyone else.

16:23.240 --> 16:25.071
The best thing
I have to offer a woman...

16:25.240 --> 16:27.276
...is the same thing
you offer a woman. You.

16:27.440 --> 16:29.715
Yeah, but I'm all tied up, Mac.
I'm using me.

16:29.880 --> 16:32.519
Come on. It'll be fun.

16:32.680 --> 16:34.989
- You like fun.
- Fun?

16:35.160 --> 16:38.630
Interviewing a man-hating, embittered
New England spinster librarian?

16:38.800 --> 16:40.233
How do you know what she's like?

16:40.400 --> 16:42.675
Who else would write a book called
<i>Down With Love?</i>

16:42.840 --> 16:45.877
You don't have to be a Nazi
rocket scientist to figure that out.

16:46.040 --> 16:47.871
Catch, please, please, please, please.

16:50.840 --> 16:53.149
I hope you won't be disappointed.

17:20.560 --> 17:24.791
Oh, Vikki, it's adorable.

17:25.359 --> 17:26.634
[PHONE RINGING]

17:27.400 --> 17:30.836
My first New York phone call.

17:31.000 --> 17:32.513
It must be <i>Know</i> magazine.

17:32.680 --> 17:34.636
No one else has your number.

17:35.760 --> 17:38.354
- It must be Catcher Block.
- Oh!

17:41.560 --> 17:44.358
- This is Barbara Novak.
- This is Catcher Block.

17:44.520 --> 17:48.035
Catcher Block? Catcher Block?

17:48.200 --> 17:50.839
<i>- Know</i> magazine.
- Oh, yes, of course.

17:51.000 --> 17:52.479
What can I do for you, Mr. Block?

17:52.640 --> 17:53.629
[LAUGHING]

17:53.800 --> 17:55.916
I think it's what
I can do for you, Miss Novak.

17:56.080 --> 17:58.594
I'd like to invite you to lunch
to discuss your book.

17:58.760 --> 18:02.150
Well, that sounds very nice,
but I'll have to check my schedule...

18:02.320 --> 18:03.639
...to see when I'm available.

18:03.800 --> 18:06.997
We've already ordered. Can you be
in the Mahogany Room in 10 minutes?

18:07.160 --> 18:09.674
I'm afraid that will be impossible,
Mr. Block.

18:09.840 --> 18:11.239
Well, some other time, then.

18:11.400 --> 18:14.153
Right, I'll see you in 15.

18:15.080 --> 18:17.036
[SCREAMING]

18:17.600 --> 18:21.149
Catch, you are the best friend a guy
with 20 diagnosed neuroses ever had.

18:21.320 --> 18:24.198
We've been friends a long time.
I knew you when you had 12.

18:24.360 --> 18:29.036
Oh, this is great. I'll be right back.
Gotta go put in my shoe lifts.

18:32.920 --> 18:35.673
- Guess who?
- As if I'd need to guess.

18:35.840 --> 18:38.070
- Tell me my name.
- Tell me you love me.

18:38.240 --> 18:39.878
Blimey, Catch, you know I love you.

18:40.040 --> 18:42.235
And I love you too, Gwendolyn.

18:42.400 --> 18:44.072
[CHUCKLING]

18:47.880 --> 18:49.950
- How long's your layover?
- Never long enough.

18:50.120 --> 18:52.918
There's always time for a matinee.

19:44.680 --> 19:45.874
Well, hello, Peter.

19:46.040 --> 19:48.600
Barbara Novak, Peter McMannus.

19:48.760 --> 19:50.830
Nice to meet you, Mr. McMannus.

19:51.000 --> 19:52.274
VIKKl:
Where's Mr. Block?

19:52.440 --> 19:54.476
Yes, Mr. McMannus,
where's Mr. Block?

19:54.640 --> 19:56.039
I don't know.

19:56.200 --> 20:00.591
- Henri, where is Mr. Block?
- I don't know.

20:00.760 --> 20:04.309
- Mr. Block for you, Mr. McMannus.
- Ah.

20:05.480 --> 20:07.311
Here he is now.

20:10.440 --> 20:12.351
- Catcher.
CATCHER: <i>Mac.</i>

20:12.520 --> 20:16.229
- Where are you?
- <i>Something sprung up. Is she there?</i>

20:16.400 --> 20:19.551
PETER: Yes, she is.
- <i>Let me speak to the spinster.</i>

20:19.720 --> 20:22.996
Mr. Block would like to speak with you.

20:26.360 --> 20:29.272
- This is Barbara Novak.
- I'm so sorry, Miss Novak.

20:29.440 --> 20:30.873
The darndest thing.

20:31.040 --> 20:34.032
I was waiting for you at the bar
and a little English foxhound...

20:34.200 --> 20:37.272
...walked right in, came up to me
and started nuzzling me.

20:37.440 --> 20:40.512
She seemed so lost, and didn't
want to go with anyone else...

20:40.680 --> 20:45.117
...so I just had to take care of her.
- Mr. Block, that is so thoughtful.

20:45.280 --> 20:48.272
I remember reading that
the true test of a man's character...

20:48.440 --> 20:50.749
...is how he treats
a defenseless creature.

20:50.920 --> 20:54.230
Tell me, Mr. Block,
how is the little bitch now?

20:54.400 --> 20:58.837
Well, I've got her all nestled in a box,
but I don't think she'll be content...

20:59.000 --> 21:00.353
...until I'm holding her.

21:00.520 --> 21:03.239
Miss Novak, could we
rain check until dinner?

21:03.400 --> 21:04.992
Of course.

21:05.160 --> 21:10.188
- Well, goodbye, Mr. Block. Until dinner.
- Goodbye.

21:27.360 --> 21:28.873
This is Barbara Novak.

21:29.040 --> 21:33.079
Miss Novak, I am so sorry,
the darndest thing.

21:33.240 --> 21:34.514
Yes, Mr. Block.

21:34.680 --> 21:37.399
I'm out in the park with
my little French poodle...

21:37.560 --> 21:41.189
...and she's just not ready to go in yet,
if you know what I mean.

21:41.360 --> 21:42.759
Oh, I do.

21:42.920 --> 21:46.310
But here's a little advice
from a farm girl to a city boy.

21:46.480 --> 21:49.392
You'll find that if you stick
a little twig in her bottom...

21:49.560 --> 21:52.757
...she'll remember why she
went out with you in the first place.

21:52.920 --> 21:54.751
I'll keep that in mind.

21:54.920 --> 21:59.311
Miss Novak, I hate to ask, but could we
rain check until breakfast?

21:59.480 --> 22:03.393
Of course. Goodbye, Mr. Block.
Until breakfast.

22:06.200 --> 22:08.634
[CROWD CHEERING]

22:09.600 --> 22:13.388
I just don't know.
It's not like Catch to be late.

22:13.560 --> 22:16.677
No, he usually calls to cancel
right on time.

22:16.840 --> 22:20.958
Oh, Barbara, I'm sure he'll call.
I mean come.

22:21.800 --> 22:24.872
Elke and I missed you at lunch
yesterday, Gwendolyn.

22:25.040 --> 22:29.636
Oh, I took in a matinee
with Catcher Block.

22:31.360 --> 22:33.157
Is that so?

22:33.320 --> 22:35.754
Elke and I missed you
at dinner last night, Yvette.

22:35.920 --> 22:38.559
I took in a night game
with Catcher Block.

22:41.840 --> 22:43.876
I told him I'd give up flying for him.

22:44.040 --> 22:45.359
YVETTE:
I did too.

22:45.520 --> 22:48.557
- Now I wonder if he ever loved me.
- I wonder if he even cared.

22:50.440 --> 22:52.158
I wonder what's keeping Elke.

23:03.120 --> 23:04.599
This is Barbara Novak.

23:04.760 --> 23:07.593
I'm so sorry, Miss Novak.
The darndest thing.

23:07.760 --> 23:10.638
I got waylaid by the sweetest
Swedish Lapphund...

23:10.800 --> 23:14.031
...who kept me up half the night,
and I'm afraid I'm still in bed.

23:14.200 --> 23:17.510
My, you do get way laid.

23:17.680 --> 23:19.910
- Would you care for another beverage?
- Thank you.

23:20.080 --> 23:22.640
- I beg your pardon?
- I was saying thank you, Miss Novak.

23:22.800 --> 23:24.472
You are very understanding.

23:24.640 --> 23:26.517
Could we rain check until lunch?

23:26.680 --> 23:30.593
Oh, Mr. Block,
you can take your rain check...

23:30.760 --> 23:33.513
...and as we say
on the farm at harvest time...

23:33.680 --> 23:36.399
...put it where the sun does not shine.

23:36.560 --> 23:40.155
Miss Novak, if you're looking to get
dinner, then just say so.

23:40.320 --> 23:43.676
Oh, Mr. Block.

23:43.840 --> 23:48.960
I wouldn't meet with you
in 100 years.

23:49.120 --> 23:53.398
Goodbye, Mr. Block. Forever!

23:59.000 --> 24:01.434
Mr. McMannus,
thank you for your trouble.

24:01.600 --> 24:03.477
Not at all.

24:03.640 --> 24:06.791
Vikki, I'll call a taxi.

24:10.480 --> 24:13.278
- Guess this means we're through.
- Oh, it's sad, isn't it?

24:13.440 --> 24:16.591
This is the first time I've eliminated
having a future with a man...

24:16.760 --> 24:19.035
...before we've had the chance
to have had a past.

24:19.200 --> 24:21.668
Goodbye, Mr. McMannus.

24:28.240 --> 24:29.434
[BIG BAND MUSIC PLAYS]

24:29.600 --> 24:31.636
PETER:
It was nice while it lasted.

24:31.800 --> 24:35.509
I haven't had dinner and breakfast with
the same woman since I had a nanny.

24:35.680 --> 24:38.353
I'm sorry, Peter, but Vikki
is not the only girl for you.

24:38.520 --> 24:39.953
That's why I brought you here.

24:40.120 --> 24:44.159
You brought me here
because we're buddies, right?

24:44.320 --> 24:45.435
Bosom buddies.

24:45.600 --> 24:47.272
[CROWD WHISTLING]

24:59.320 --> 25:02.710
- Get a load of those rockets.
- Here's to antigravity.

25:02.880 --> 25:04.791
Stay with me, buddy.
You'll get the spins.

25:04.960 --> 25:07.599
And whatever you do,
don't close your eyes.

25:07.760 --> 25:10.399
Don't close your eyes.

25:10.960 --> 25:14.635
Open your eyes. Open your eyes.

25:15.840 --> 25:18.354
Ta-da! It's your book.

25:19.680 --> 25:21.591
VIKKl:
On sale, Scribners Fifth Avenue.

25:22.360 --> 25:24.476
One?

25:24.640 --> 25:26.358
Just one?

25:27.800 --> 25:31.110
All that work, and, and, and one.

25:31.280 --> 25:34.989
If somebody buys it,
well, then there will be none.

25:35.160 --> 25:38.152
It'll be as if it never even existed.

25:38.320 --> 25:41.596
No, no. Doubleday also has one.

25:41.760 --> 25:42.954
[CASH REGISTER RINGS]

25:43.480 --> 25:46.074
Barbara, I know you're thinking
this is a real setback...

25:46.240 --> 25:48.470
...but I promise you
I will think of something.

25:52.640 --> 25:55.234
If only we could get your book
on <i>The Ed Sullivan Show.</i>

25:55.400 --> 25:56.719
Yeah.

25:57.760 --> 26:01.912
How exactly do you get a book
on <i>The Ed Sullivan Show?</i>

26:03.840 --> 26:05.319
BARBARA:
Vikki, you're incredible.

26:05.480 --> 26:07.948
She wasn't even on the bill.
How did they fit her in?

26:08.120 --> 26:10.759
Oh, the best luck.
The Singing Nun fell off her scooter...

26:10.920 --> 26:12.990
...coming across the Triborough Bridge.

26:13.160 --> 26:16.357
I guess somebody up there likes me.

26:16.520 --> 26:18.272
ED SULLIVAN:
<i>- A really big surprise.</i>

26:18.440 --> 26:24.117
<i>Because it coincides with the arrival</i>
<i>of a new book,</i> Down With Love...

26:24.280 --> 26:27.716
<i>... which this week is at your</i>
<i>booksellers from coast to coast.</i>

26:27.880 --> 26:33.830
<i>We have a very, very special friend</i>
<i>of our show to do a song of that book.</i>

26:34.000 --> 26:40.439
<i>Now, I want a really big, warm</i>
<i>welcome for Judy Garland.</i>

26:40.600 --> 26:42.909
[CROWD CLAPPING]

26:46.120 --> 26:49.351
[SINGS "DOWN WITH LOVE"]

27:06.840 --> 27:09.035
[BO Y LAUGHING]

27:25.200 --> 27:27.873
Yes, ma'am.
<i>Down With Love</i> by Barbara Novak.

27:28.040 --> 27:30.190
It's called <i>Down With Love</i>
by Barbara Novak.

27:50.400 --> 27:52.789
[CHATTERING]

27:55.760 --> 27:57.876
[DOORBELL RINGS]

28:03.960 --> 28:06.030
[BICYCLE BELLS RINGING]

28:31.240 --> 28:33.151
[CASH REGISTER RINGING]

28:37.120 --> 28:39.236
[CHILDREN YELLING]

28:45.800 --> 28:47.438
Ow!

28:56.640 --> 28:59.438
[SCREAMING]

29:01.320 --> 29:04.153
[CROWD CLAPPING]

29:24.640 --> 29:26.073
You said she was a spinster.

29:26.240 --> 29:28.470
I never used the word spinster
in my life.

29:28.640 --> 29:32.394
Okay, once. When I told my mother it
was incorrect to call her son a spinster.

29:32.560 --> 29:35.074
- You said she was a brunette.
- I did not.

29:35.240 --> 29:38.357
She didn't sound blond on the phone.
Do you still wanna date Vikki?

29:38.520 --> 29:40.511
Of course. You think
I wanna die a spinster?

29:40.680 --> 29:42.511
Call her. Tell her I'll do
the cover story.

29:42.680 --> 29:44.671
Oh, Catch, you are the best friend
a guy...

29:44.840 --> 29:47.638
Just call.

29:47.840 --> 29:51.992
MAN: Not since Johann Gutenberg's
invention of the printing press...

29:52.160 --> 29:55.596
...which changed forever the landscape
of man's destiny...

29:55.760 --> 29:59.673
...has one book reached so many
and achieved so much.

29:59.840 --> 30:03.389
Reminding all of us here today
of the noble goal...

30:03.560 --> 30:07.997
...which called us to toil in the field
of publishing to begin with:

30:08.360 --> 30:09.998
Sales.

30:10.160 --> 30:13.994
So here's to Banner House's
new number one author...

30:14.160 --> 30:17.755
...and our new number one editor.

30:18.360 --> 30:20.669
Say cheers, everyone.

30:20.840 --> 30:22.637
Cheers.

30:23.360 --> 30:25.112
VIKKl:
Those men are livid, B.N.

30:25.280 --> 30:27.191
You're a hit. You're bigger
than the pill.

30:27.360 --> 30:30.193
Oh, talk about big, V.H.

30:30.360 --> 30:33.272
This office is huge. Congratulations.

30:33.440 --> 30:35.396
We did it.

30:35.560 --> 30:38.279
Well, hello, Gladys.

30:38.440 --> 30:39.589
You look wonderful.

30:39.760 --> 30:43.196
As you told me, Barbara,
it's never too late.

30:43.360 --> 30:48.639
Oh, Vikki, Peter McMannus called again.
Now it's every half-hour.

30:49.040 --> 30:50.837
Tell him we're too busy.

30:51.240 --> 30:53.879
What do you mean? Too busy?

30:54.040 --> 30:56.998
You know what it means.
They hate us.

30:57.160 --> 31:00.277
CATCHER: Too busy? Kennedy,
Khrushchev and Castro...

31:00.440 --> 31:04.069
...weren't too busy during the Cuban
Missile Crisis to sit down and talk to me.

31:04.240 --> 31:07.437
But this <i>Down With Love</i> chick
is too busy?

31:07.640 --> 31:09.995
Doing what? Eating chocolate?

31:10.160 --> 31:12.549
MAN OVER TV:
<i>I'm sorry, panel, you've been stumped.</i>

31:12.720 --> 31:14.915
<i>The author of the bestseller</i>
Down With Love...

31:15.120 --> 31:17.714
- It's Novak!
- <i>... Barbara Novak.</i>

31:17.920 --> 31:18.909
[CROWD CLAPPING]

31:19.080 --> 31:21.799
<i>Barbara, I know every woman bought</i>
<i>your book. And every man...</i>

31:21.960 --> 31:25.191
<i>... sneaked out and bought it to find out</i>
<i>what their women were reading.</i>

31:25.360 --> 31:27.476
<i>Oh, well, that's when the sales doubled.</i>

31:27.680 --> 31:29.875
<i>But then they tripled.</i>
<i>How did that happen?</i>

31:30.080 --> 31:33.709
<i>It seems that church groups</i>
<i>in the Bible belt were so zealous...</i>

31:33.880 --> 31:37.475
<i>... about being seen burning my book</i>
<i>that every time they had a bonfire...</i>

31:37.640 --> 31:40.950
<i>... they would call the next day and</i>
<i>reorder, so they could have another one.</i>

31:41.120 --> 31:43.076
[CHUCKLING]

31:45.160 --> 31:47.993
<i>Now, I've heard a lot of talk</i>
<i>about Chapter 8...</i>

31:48.160 --> 31:51.197
<i>... about the worst kind of man,</i>
<i>the kind every woman should avoid.</i>

31:51.360 --> 31:53.191
<i>- What's that title again?</i>
<i>- Oh, yes.</i>

31:53.360 --> 31:56.716
<i>Men Who Change Women As</i>
<i>Often As They Change Their Shirts.</i>

31:57.320 --> 32:01.029
EMCEE: <i>And have you met a lot of</i>
<i>that kind of man in your research?</i>

32:01.240 --> 32:03.549
<i>You're not asking me to name names,</i>
<i>are you?</i>

32:03.760 --> 32:05.239
<i>No, of course not.</i>

32:05.440 --> 32:06.873
[BARBARA CHUCKLING]

32:07.040 --> 32:10.032
<i>- Catcher Block.</i>
CROWD: <i>Oh!</i>

32:16.160 --> 32:17.752
Wow.

32:19.360 --> 32:21.396
Four million women in the naked city...

32:21.560 --> 32:25.792
...and the one you let get away, the one
you had to get on the bad side of...

32:25.960 --> 32:30.590
...is the woman all the other four million
are listening to.

32:30.800 --> 32:32.199
[PETER CHUCKLING]

32:32.360 --> 32:35.272
You blew it, buddy.

32:35.440 --> 32:40.753
The age of Catcher Block, ladies' man,
man's man, man about town, is over.

32:40.960 --> 32:42.678
The king is dead.

32:42.840 --> 32:46.389
I hate to spoil your fun, Mac, but
the four million women I go out with...

32:46.560 --> 32:48.391
...don't listen to Barbara Novak.

32:48.560 --> 32:50.198
[PHONE RINGS]

32:52.160 --> 32:53.991
Hello.

32:54.160 --> 32:57.948
Hey, Gwendolyn, baby.
Where are you?

32:58.440 --> 33:01.557
Well, then get out of the airport.
We have reservations for 10:00.

33:02.440 --> 33:06.831
Well, you can't sit in the terminal till
3 a.m. Aren't you gonna get hungry?

33:07.040 --> 33:11.875
No, I'm pretty full. Besides, I have
to catch up on some reading.

33:12.080 --> 33:16.153
Reading? Reading what?

33:18.560 --> 33:21.028
Good night, Gwendolyn.

33:25.760 --> 33:29.514
What's the matter, Catch?
Lose another one?

33:29.720 --> 33:32.996
I am going to bury that Novak broad...

33:33.160 --> 33:36.869
...and turn this crazy upside-down-
with-Iove world right side up again.

33:37.040 --> 33:40.191
I'm gonna write the exposé of
the century, so the world will know...

33:40.360 --> 33:43.079
...once and for all that deep down,
all women are the same.

33:43.240 --> 33:45.470
They all want the same thing:
Love and marriage.

33:45.640 --> 33:50.555
Even Miss Barbara <i>"Down With Love"</i>
Novak. And I am going to prove it.

33:50.760 --> 33:53.149
How? Novak won't even see you.

33:53.760 --> 33:58.231
That's right. That's why Novak
won't even see me coming.

34:05.560 --> 34:07.994
Barbara, you're not dressed.
Aren't you coming?

34:08.159 --> 34:10.594
No. I'm just gonna stay in tonight.

34:10.760 --> 34:12.795
Why? Because you don't have a date?

34:12.960 --> 34:16.190
My date's a quarterback with 27
teammates. I'm sure he can fix you up.

34:16.400 --> 34:21.474
I'm sure he couldn't.
I am persona non grata to all men.

34:21.639 --> 34:24.393
I can't even get picked up
by a taxi driver.

34:24.560 --> 34:27.916
Now, this is crazy.
All of this fame and success...

34:28.080 --> 34:31.516
...and Miss Sex à la Carte is the only
woman who can't have sex à la carte.

34:31.679 --> 34:33.511
At least not on this earth.

34:33.679 --> 34:37.275
Maybe we can find you an astronaut
who's been in orbit the past two weeks.

34:37.440 --> 34:40.431
It's all right, Vikki. I'm perfectly content
on my own.

34:40.639 --> 34:44.632
Well, when it comes to not needing
a man, you wrote the book.

34:45.880 --> 34:47.313
[DOOR CLOSES]

35:06.680 --> 35:07.669
- Taxi!
- Wait a minute.

35:07.840 --> 35:11.150
- I have to pick up my dry cleaning.
- Can't. Gotta go back to the office.

35:11.320 --> 35:13.515
Skip in Research is doing a fact-check
on Novak.

35:13.680 --> 35:16.797
Who she knows, where she goes, what
she likes for dinner, à la carte.

35:16.960 --> 35:20.396
Two minutes? I waited for you
to eat your hot dog.

35:21.960 --> 35:24.872
You're right. I'll pick up your cleaning.
Go back to the office.

35:25.080 --> 35:26.479
Oh, but l...

35:26.800 --> 35:27.789
Ow!

35:29.400 --> 35:32.358
Oh, make sure they starch the socks.

35:50.640 --> 35:51.755
[BELL DINGING]

35:51.920 --> 35:53.831
DRY CLEANER:
I'm getting it.

35:54.040 --> 35:56.679
- You iron.
- No, you iron...

35:56.840 --> 36:00.037
...and I'll spend all day up front
kibitzing with the customers.

36:00.560 --> 36:02.516
We're equal now.

36:02.720 --> 36:04.551
Again with that book.

36:12.560 --> 36:14.516
Hello, Novak.

36:14.680 --> 36:17.478
BARBARA:
Hello, Mrs. Litzer.

36:17.640 --> 36:19.358
Where's Mr. Litzer?

36:19.560 --> 36:21.471
He's ironing.

36:22.160 --> 36:25.197
Irving, say hello to Novak.

36:25.840 --> 36:27.432
Hello, Novak.

36:27.840 --> 36:29.193
I'll get your things, dear.

36:29.360 --> 36:31.510
BARBARA:
Thank you.

36:33.360 --> 36:35.954
Yours too, mister.

36:43.640 --> 36:46.871
Pardon me, miss, but you
sure look familiar. Are you...?

36:47.040 --> 36:48.792
Yes, I am.

36:48.960 --> 36:52.396
Well, I'll be a monkey's uncle.
Wait till I tell the folks back home...

36:52.560 --> 36:56.792
...I took my clothes to the same
dry cleaners as Miss Kim Novik.

36:56.960 --> 36:59.394
No, no, my name is Novak.

36:59.560 --> 37:01.994
Oh, that's right. Miss Kim Novak.

37:02.160 --> 37:06.517
No, no, I'm not Kim Novak.
I'm Barbara Novak.

37:06.680 --> 37:07.829
Oh.

37:08.400 --> 37:11.153
Oh, well, that doesn't ring a bell.

37:12.160 --> 37:14.037
You mean you've never heard of me?

37:14.240 --> 37:15.468
Oh, I'm sorry.

37:15.640 --> 37:17.870
Oh, no. No, don't be.

37:18.040 --> 37:20.349
I find it very refreshing.

37:21.240 --> 37:23.674
You, Mr. Absent-minded Professor.

37:23.840 --> 37:25.990
You left a lot of things
in your pockets.

37:26.160 --> 37:28.628
Why, thank you, ma'am.

37:29.760 --> 37:31.990
Excuse me. I'm sorry.

37:32.160 --> 37:34.993
Do you mean that you've never heard
of my book...

37:35.160 --> 37:37.833
...the worldwide sensation,
<i>Down With Love?</i>

37:38.040 --> 37:40.554
No, ma'am, I have not.

37:41.040 --> 37:43.918
But lately, I've been out of this world.

37:44.120 --> 37:49.194
Oh, look, my NASA security badge.
I've been looking all over for that.

37:49.360 --> 37:52.432
- You're an astronaut?
- Why, yes, I am.

37:52.640 --> 37:55.518
Well, what's your name?
Maybe I've heard of you.

37:57.120 --> 37:58.394
Zip.

37:58.840 --> 38:01.149
Zip...?

38:02.720 --> 38:05.154
Martin. Major Zip Martin.

38:05.560 --> 38:08.393
Well, tell me, major...

38:08.560 --> 38:12.189
...are those parties in Cocoa Beach
as wild and uncivilized as they seem?

38:12.360 --> 38:16.399
Oh, now, I couldn't say, ma'am.
I'm not much for going to parties.

38:16.560 --> 38:21.076
My idea of a good time is to sit at home
with a good book...

38:21.240 --> 38:24.835
...and smoke my pipe.

38:26.120 --> 38:29.510
Pay later. Irving's burning the ironing.

38:29.720 --> 38:31.950
Pardon me, miss.

38:36.760 --> 38:39.399
Oh, we're stuck together.

38:39.560 --> 38:41.835
Let me fix that.

38:45.440 --> 38:48.432
There you go, Miss Novak.

38:55.720 --> 38:57.153
Well...

38:59.480 --> 39:01.232
...goodbye.

39:02.040 --> 39:04.873
One, two, three, four.

39:05.040 --> 39:06.758
Zip?

39:06.960 --> 39:08.757
Yes, Miss Novak?

39:08.960 --> 39:12.589
Well, I don't suppose that
you're staying in New York?

39:12.800 --> 39:14.472
Why, yes, I am.

39:14.640 --> 39:17.598
NASA sent me here to work
on a special project.

39:17.760 --> 39:21.548
- A top-secret project.
- Oh?

39:21.960 --> 39:25.270
- Can you keep a secret?
- Yes.

39:25.480 --> 39:26.629
Me too.

39:26.840 --> 39:29.718
Gee, it sure seems like we got
a lot in common.

39:29.920 --> 39:32.798
Why, yes, it does.

39:32.960 --> 39:36.475
It might be nice to see
just what we have in common.

39:36.640 --> 39:39.950
And what we have that's different.

39:40.120 --> 39:41.872
I'm sorry?

39:42.080 --> 39:47.313
Would you like to go to my place and
get to know each other a little better?

39:47.520 --> 39:50.080
- A little better?
- A lot better.

39:50.280 --> 39:54.159
- A lot better than what?
- All the way better.

39:54.960 --> 39:59.192
Oh, gee. No, now, I couldn't do that.

39:59.360 --> 40:02.193
Why, I couldn't get to know you
all the way better...

40:02.360 --> 40:05.272
...until I knew you much, much better.

40:05.440 --> 40:10.230
Do you think that you know me well
enough to let me buy you a drink?

40:10.640 --> 40:12.232
Well...

40:13.400 --> 40:16.915
I'd sure love a Tang.

40:24.960 --> 40:26.598
Lose another pair of glasses?

40:26.760 --> 40:28.398
PETER:
No, I'm keeping a low profile.

40:28.560 --> 40:30.790
Vikki's over there with some guy.

40:30.960 --> 40:33.793
That's not some guy. That's
Johnny Trementus, the quarterback.

40:33.960 --> 40:36.428
Fourteen hundred and thirty-two
complete passes.

40:36.640 --> 40:39.279
Is he going for 1433?

40:39.440 --> 40:43.149
Well, Vikki's left herself wide open,
but Trementus surprisingly fumbles.

40:43.320 --> 40:45.959
Now what's he doing?
In layman's terms.

40:46.120 --> 40:48.076
He's leaving. Now's your chance.

40:48.280 --> 40:50.157
I can't go over there. She hates me.

40:50.360 --> 40:51.998
She doesn't hate you. She hates me.

40:52.160 --> 40:54.594
Now, stop warming the bench
and get in the game.

40:54.760 --> 40:58.548
Once you run my Novak exposé, she will
hate you, and the clock will run out.

40:58.760 --> 41:00.876
Can't you get off your Novak warpath?

41:01.040 --> 41:02.871
Nope. I've got her surrounded.

41:03.040 --> 41:06.112
And it won't take a surprise attack
to enter her teepee.

41:06.320 --> 41:08.595
I'm telling you, Kemosabe,
you want big wampum?

41:08.760 --> 41:09.875
Make Vikki love you now.

41:10.040 --> 41:14.352
Okay, okay, enough
with the football talk. I'm going.

41:18.160 --> 41:20.276
- Here you are, <i>Monsieur</i> Block.
- Thanks, Henri.

41:20.440 --> 41:24.149
Only, from now on it's Maj. Zip Martin.

41:24.760 --> 41:27.274
Spread the word to the other maître d's,
the doormen...

41:27.440 --> 41:29.396
...theater ushers and taxi drivers.

41:29.640 --> 41:34.475
<i>Oui, oui.</i> Done, major.

41:36.040 --> 41:40.033
It'll be all right, McMannus.
Just be normal. Be cool.

41:43.640 --> 41:46.108
Hello, Vikki.

41:46.320 --> 41:48.959
Hello, Peter.

41:54.240 --> 41:56.196
Are you in love
with that football player?

41:56.960 --> 42:02.273
Not anymore. He only wanted one thing,
to slip me his manuscript.

42:02.440 --> 42:05.955
He didn't even have the professional
courtesy to try and seduce me first.

42:06.160 --> 42:08.879
The men who resent my success
won't give me the time of day.

42:09.040 --> 42:12.749
And the men who respect my success
won't give me the time of night.

42:13.240 --> 42:16.198
I don't know about other men,
but I swear if I had the chance...

42:16.360 --> 42:20.035
...I would respect you and resent you
night and day and day and night.

42:20.240 --> 42:22.356
- Peter, you would?
- You bet.

42:22.560 --> 42:24.755
You're on.

42:28.840 --> 42:31.877
Oh, Zip, isn't this exciting?

42:32.040 --> 42:36.192
We must be the only two people in New
York who haven't seen <i>Camelot</i> yet.

42:36.360 --> 42:39.591
You're not just being nice?
You really haven't seen it either?

42:39.760 --> 42:44.436
Oh, I can honestly say I have
never seen this show.

42:44.600 --> 42:46.750
[ORCHESTRA PLAYING]

43:46.200 --> 43:48.919
[CROWD YELLING]

43:49.080 --> 43:50.752
[BELL RINGING]

43:51.200 --> 43:53.111
[BASEBALL BAT HITS BALL]

44:08.680 --> 44:09.669
[INTERCOM BUZZING]

44:09.840 --> 44:11.876
WOMAN: <i>Mr. Block, Mr. McNulty</i>
<i>to see you.</i>

44:12.040 --> 44:14.429
Send him in.

44:16.040 --> 44:19.396
McNulty, good. Look, this should cover
your up-front expenses.

44:19.560 --> 44:22.472
I want you to go up to Maine,
get me all the dirt on Novak.

44:22.680 --> 44:25.877
No girl like that would swear off love
to get ahead in the work force.

44:26.040 --> 44:28.190
Somewhere, sometime,
some guy hurt her.

44:28.400 --> 44:31.915
Now, I need to find him, so I can prove
I'm right and nail my exposé.

44:32.120 --> 44:35.192
Gladly. That broad's book
is bad for business.

44:35.360 --> 44:37.590
Husbands don't want their wives
tailed anymore.

44:37.760 --> 44:41.230
They know if she's sneaking out now,
she's just looking for a job.

44:41.400 --> 44:42.389
[PHONE RINGS]

44:42.960 --> 44:48.671
Hello. Mac. Mac. Mac, calm down.

44:48.840 --> 44:50.751
Okay, I'll be right over.

44:51.440 --> 44:54.989
- Quick, taste my sauce. Too tart?
- This is your big emergency?

44:55.160 --> 44:58.550
Yes. I invited Vikki to dinner.
It has to be perfect...

44:58.720 --> 45:01.553
...so she'll find me irresistible,
and I can make my big move.

45:01.720 --> 45:05.269
You could've made your big move
three weeks ago, Mac. I keep telling you.

45:05.440 --> 45:09.194
That's these <i>Down With Love</i> girls'
claim to fame. One date, no waiting.

45:09.360 --> 45:13.069
These <i>Down With Love</i> girls may be used
to having sex the way a man does...

45:13.240 --> 45:16.277
...but I'm not. Too sweet?

45:18.160 --> 45:21.232
So I guess you and Novak
have been very down with love.

45:22.000 --> 45:25.913
I mean, you've had, what,
29 dates in 23 days?

45:26.080 --> 45:28.992
Yeah, but I'm trying to get her not
to want to have sex with me.

45:29.160 --> 45:32.311
These days you gotta play your cards
right to get a girl to say no.

45:32.520 --> 45:34.909
Or maybe you just like spending time
with her.

45:35.560 --> 45:38.791
Maybe the necessity
of all this chastity and monogamy...

45:38.960 --> 45:42.589
...has made you realize that Barbara
Novak is your ideal potential lover.

45:42.800 --> 45:45.553
Come back to Earth, buddy boy.
Your cake's burning.

45:45.720 --> 45:46.709
[OVEN BUZZING]

45:51.760 --> 45:54.718
So this is how a guy like you
does it, huh?

45:54.880 --> 45:57.599
No, I don't do it. If I did do it,
I'd do what I'm doing...

45:57.760 --> 45:59.796
...which reminds me of something
I didn't do.

45:59.960 --> 46:03.077
- I have to call Vikki with my address.
- I've got a better idea.

46:03.240 --> 46:05.390
Invite Vikki to my place,
make like it's yours.

46:05.560 --> 46:07.596
You know where I keep the spare key.

46:07.760 --> 46:10.593
You'd let me use the key you leave out
for your girlfriends?

46:10.760 --> 46:14.435
Somebody might as well. It's gathering
dust since Novak hit the bestseller list.

46:14.600 --> 46:17.194
But I invited Vikki
for a home-cooked meal.

46:17.360 --> 46:18.873
Trust me.

46:19.040 --> 46:24.273
Ten minutes in my apartment,
and you'll both forget all about dinner.

46:24.440 --> 46:26.396
Ten minutes?

46:26.560 --> 46:29.028
Ten minutes.

46:29.360 --> 46:30.952
[PHONE RINGING]

46:43.160 --> 46:45.879
- Hello?
- Hello, Barbara, it's Zip.

46:46.040 --> 46:47.678
Hello, Zip.

46:47.840 --> 46:51.594
I was wondering if I could ask you
to do me a very special favor.

46:51.760 --> 46:53.796
Sure, Zip, anything.

46:53.960 --> 46:55.712
Well, I know we'd planned to go out...

46:55.880 --> 46:58.872
...but, well, I thought it might be fun
to stay in.

46:59.040 --> 47:02.077
I'm in the mood
for a home-cooked meal.

47:02.240 --> 47:06.472
Maj. Martin, I have no desire
to stay cooped up in the kitchen...

47:06.640 --> 47:10.189
...slaving over a hot stove
and a sink full of dirty dishes.

47:10.360 --> 47:14.069
Oh, no, Barbara, you misunderstood.

47:14.440 --> 47:18.194
When I said a home-cooked meal,
I meant at my place.

47:18.360 --> 47:20.794
I wanted to serve you.

47:20.960 --> 47:26.592
BARBARA: Oh, Zip, no man has
ever done this for me before.

47:27.440 --> 47:30.193
- How thoughtful.
- Well.

47:30.360 --> 47:31.679
And considerate.

47:31.840 --> 47:33.478
It's my pleasure.

47:33.640 --> 47:37.474
Oh, no. No, no, it's mine.

47:37.640 --> 47:39.676
So you'd like to come?

47:39.840 --> 47:44.197
Oh, yes. Yes, yes.

47:44.560 --> 47:47.233
I can't wait.

47:50.960 --> 47:53.269
Seventy-third and Park. And Barbara?

47:53.440 --> 47:54.998
Yes, Zip.

47:55.160 --> 47:57.879
Thank you for being so flexible.

47:58.040 --> 48:01.430
No, Zip, thank you.

48:18.040 --> 48:20.600
Oh, Zip.

48:20.760 --> 48:24.230
Everything looks divine.

48:25.440 --> 48:27.476
I have that funny feeling
that you've done...

48:27.640 --> 48:30.279
...quite a bit of entertaining
for two here.

48:30.440 --> 48:33.273
Oh, I can honestly say
that, until you...

48:33.440 --> 48:36.989
...I haven't done any entertaining
for two here at all.

48:37.160 --> 48:39.390
Well, you're certainly not
the average astronaut.

48:39.560 --> 48:43.439
Oh, I get so tired
of all that freeze-dried food.

48:43.640 --> 48:47.997
After a steady diet of pellet steak
and potato tablets...

48:48.160 --> 48:52.358
...you yearn for something hot
to sink your teeth into.

48:55.960 --> 48:59.350
Well, you've whetted my appetite.

49:00.160 --> 49:02.958
It's not just your cooking.

49:04.560 --> 49:08.189
You are so well-rounded.

49:08.360 --> 49:14.799
Your collection of art and antiques.
You've made a real home here.

49:15.000 --> 49:18.310
Well, Earth still is my favorite planet.

49:18.760 --> 49:22.275
- No, I meant here, in New York.
- Oh.

49:22.440 --> 49:25.989
Most bachelors in this city are
only interested in an apartment...

49:26.160 --> 49:29.072
...that comes fully loaded
with every gadget and contraption...

49:29.240 --> 49:32.789
...man has invented to snare a woman.

49:35.200 --> 49:39.193
I don't understand this, Peter. How
does a person lose their built-in bar?

49:39.400 --> 49:40.389
[CHUCKLING]

49:40.560 --> 49:44.189
I swear. It was here a minute ago.

49:46.880 --> 49:48.108
Ow!

49:57.240 --> 50:00.073
Hey, found it.

50:00.240 --> 50:02.196
Vikki?

50:02.360 --> 50:04.271
Where are you?

50:04.640 --> 50:07.791
VIKKl: I don't know.
- Ah!

50:15.760 --> 50:18.877
Your couch was all over me
like some animal.

50:19.040 --> 50:21.395
Who knew you were so dangerous.

50:21.600 --> 50:23.397
PETER:
I'm sorry.

50:23.560 --> 50:25.676
I know I seem a little disoriented.

50:25.840 --> 50:28.673
I guess I tasted too much sherry
while I was cooking.

50:28.840 --> 50:32.674
You cooked for me? No man
has ever done that for me before.

50:32.840 --> 50:35.479
I'm famished.

50:35.640 --> 50:40.668
Actually I didn't cook. Here.
At my apartment. For us.

50:41.520 --> 50:46.196
I cooked at Catch's apartment for Catch.

50:46.560 --> 50:49.791
- Oh.
- But you've only been here a minute.

50:49.960 --> 50:54.158
Let's make it 10 and see
if we forget all about dinner.

50:58.960 --> 51:01.679
- Are those your parents?
- No, those are Catch's parents.

51:02.000 --> 51:05.549
Why do you have a picture
of Catch's parents?

51:06.760 --> 51:08.955
Let's listen to some music.

51:22.440 --> 51:24.795
[LOUD MUSIC PLAYS]

51:30.240 --> 51:31.958
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

51:32.400 --> 51:34.277
- Oh!
- Oh!

51:36.320 --> 51:37.309
VIKKl: Oh!
- Ah!

51:39.400 --> 51:40.435
[GASPING]

51:41.760 --> 51:43.159
Oh!

51:44.520 --> 51:47.830
I can't do this for eight more minutes.
Let's go eat.

51:48.520 --> 51:49.509
[VIKKI SCREAMS]

51:50.600 --> 51:52.158
[SHATTERING AND CLANGING]

51:54.960 --> 51:56.951
CATCHER: How's that?
BARBARA: Oh.

51:58.160 --> 52:00.879
CATCHER:
You tell me when it's good for you.

52:01.040 --> 52:05.272
Put your hand on it and guide me
till I got it in the right spot.

52:05.440 --> 52:09.069
BARBARA:
Almost. Almost.

52:09.240 --> 52:11.196
Oh, Zip.

52:11.360 --> 52:13.396
I've done this a lot before,
of course...

52:13.560 --> 52:17.758
...but never with such
a powerful instrument.

52:18.360 --> 52:20.749
That's it.

52:21.240 --> 52:25.153
It's perfectly clear.

52:28.240 --> 52:34.190
Oh, Zip, I've never seen anything
so beautiful in all my life.

52:34.360 --> 52:36.032
Neither have I.

52:36.240 --> 52:38.800
You're not even looking
through the telescope.

52:39.640 --> 52:41.232
I know.

52:58.720 --> 53:02.076
This chocolate soufflé is delicious, Zip.

53:02.240 --> 53:04.800
You've really outdone yourself.

53:04.960 --> 53:07.155
I wanted the perfect end
to the perfect evening.

53:07.320 --> 53:08.309
BARBARA:
Mmm.

53:08.480 --> 53:11.438
I've never been more ready
to go to bed.

53:12.840 --> 53:15.877
Oh, Zip, I'm so glad
that you feel that way.

53:16.040 --> 53:17.917
You know that I feel the same way.

53:18.120 --> 53:21.157
Well, then let's get to bed.

53:22.200 --> 53:25.158
I'll call you a taxi.

53:25.640 --> 53:27.949
Taxi?

53:29.840 --> 53:35.392
Oh, when I said bed,
you thought I meant... bed.

53:35.560 --> 53:37.994
Oh, Barbara, I'm so sorry.

53:38.160 --> 53:41.630
This is only the first time you've been
to my home, and where I come from...

53:41.800 --> 53:44.030
It's all right, Zip.

53:44.840 --> 53:46.876
It's all right.

53:47.040 --> 53:50.476
It's better this way.

53:50.680 --> 53:55.629
Let's just say good night...

53:56.840 --> 53:58.831
...and goodbye.

53:59.040 --> 54:00.792
CATCHER:
Goodbye? You mean for good?

54:00.960 --> 54:05.351
I'm afraid so, Zip.
You see, I'm beginning to feel...

54:05.840 --> 54:07.831
Well, I'm beginning to feel.

54:08.040 --> 54:10.952
Well, couldn't you give me
just one more chance?

54:11.120 --> 54:12.997
Oh, I'd like to, Zip.

54:13.160 --> 54:15.390
Really, I would.

54:15.560 --> 54:18.393
But just the fact that I'd like
to give you another chance...

54:18.560 --> 54:22.473
...is the very reason
why I absolutely must not.

54:53.760 --> 54:56.718
Okay, one more chance.

55:00.040 --> 55:02.952
I'll just...

55:38.880 --> 55:42.031
[CHATTERING]

55:46.760 --> 55:48.671
[KEYS JINGLE]

56:11.960 --> 56:13.951
- Peter?
- You rang.

56:14.120 --> 56:17.078
No, I used my key.
How did everyone else get in here?

56:17.240 --> 56:20.869
I took Vikki down to the Village
for a demitasse. Crazy.

56:21.080 --> 56:24.390
And then the coffeehouse got raided,
so I moved the scene uptown.

56:24.560 --> 56:26.278
You dig, daddy-o?

56:26.440 --> 56:28.237
Oh, I do dig.

56:28.640 --> 56:34.749
And after being grounded for 24 days,
this astronaut is ready to blast off.

56:38.440 --> 56:40.237
Ask me why I mourn.

56:40.440 --> 56:42.078
Why do you mourn, baby?

56:42.280 --> 56:44.794
I mourn because you are shrouded
in the suit and tie...

56:44.960 --> 56:47.758
...that Madison Avenue
will bury you in alive.

56:47.960 --> 56:51.350
Well, if it will cheer you up,
you can help me out of it.

57:04.960 --> 57:07.269
- Hi.
- Hi.

57:07.440 --> 57:08.953
Coffee?

57:09.120 --> 57:11.873
So this is a beatnik party.

57:12.040 --> 57:14.076
- Isn't it a gas?
- Yes.

57:14.240 --> 57:15.673
Oh, I'm so glad you called.

57:15.840 --> 57:18.149
After my date tonight,
I didn't wanna be alone.

57:18.360 --> 57:21.318
You won't need an astronaut
to find a date. Everyone's in orbit.

57:21.520 --> 57:24.193
So should I introduce myself
to the host?

57:24.360 --> 57:26.669
- Or is that too establishment?
- You know the host.

57:26.840 --> 57:28.239
This is Peter's place.

57:28.440 --> 57:30.954
- Catcher Block won't be here, will he?
- Oh, not to worry.

57:31.120 --> 57:33.111
Everyone here's a total stranger.

57:33.280 --> 57:36.750
Go throw your coat on the bed,
and let's join the bash.

57:44.360 --> 57:46.669
Oh, excuse me.

57:46.840 --> 57:49.434
- Catch.
CATCHER: Yes?

57:51.040 --> 57:53.076
Zip?

57:53.400 --> 57:54.799
CATCHER:
Barbara.

57:54.960 --> 57:57.155
Barbara, wait.

57:57.840 --> 57:59.990
Barbara.

58:00.160 --> 58:02.879
Barbara, wait. I can explain.

58:03.040 --> 58:05.600
You don't have to.
You said you were ready for bed.

58:05.760 --> 58:08.593
I'm glad you found someone you
care enough for to take to bed.

58:08.800 --> 58:11.030
But it wasn't like that.
I don't even know her.

58:11.240 --> 58:14.550
- Oh, really?
- I mean, I didn't know what I was doing.

58:14.760 --> 58:17.957
And yet her hat's off to you anyway.

58:18.160 --> 58:20.230
What?

58:30.720 --> 58:32.711
Good night, miss.

58:34.880 --> 58:37.030
Good night, Maj. Martin.

58:37.200 --> 58:39.634
CATCHER: Believe me,
I didn't know what was happening.

58:39.840 --> 58:42.718
The minute I got here,
that girl filled my pipe with tobacco...

58:42.880 --> 58:46.429
...she bought in San Francisco.
And after that, everything went hooey.

58:46.640 --> 58:50.315
- You mean she drugged you?
- All the way into that bedroom.

58:50.520 --> 58:51.794
Wait a minute.

58:51.960 --> 58:53.837
What were you doing
at a party like that?

58:54.040 --> 58:56.838
Well, I had no idea
there was going to be a party here.

58:57.000 --> 59:00.231
I got a call to tell me to come
to this publisher's apartment...

59:00.400 --> 59:03.233
...to meet some journalist who wanted
to do a cover story...

59:03.400 --> 59:07.951
...on my NASA top-secret project.
Some guy named Snitch or Snatch.

59:08.160 --> 59:10.720
- Catch? Catcher Block?
- Maybe.

59:10.880 --> 59:14.077
Anyway, I rush over here,
and that guy does not even show up.

59:14.320 --> 59:16.709
Don't you see? You were set up.

59:16.920 --> 59:18.751
- No!
- Yes.

59:19.400 --> 59:21.914
Catcher Block invited you here
under false pretenses...

59:22.080 --> 59:24.594
...so he could do
one of his famous exposés...

59:24.760 --> 59:28.230
...on how NASA's top-secret
New York project...

59:28.400 --> 59:31.392
...is just one big drug-infested
beatnik shindig.

59:31.560 --> 59:32.913
Oh, that's low.

59:33.120 --> 59:36.669
That's Catcher Block.
That's how he operates.

59:36.880 --> 59:38.916
Oh, Barbara, I'm so sorry.

59:39.120 --> 59:43.033
I just feel like such
an easily tricked hick.

59:43.200 --> 59:47.637
And then you went
and made the trick seem so obvious.

59:47.800 --> 59:52.828
Oh, Zip. I didn't mean
to make you feel bad.

59:53.680 --> 59:56.319
I didn't mean to make you feel mad.

59:57.040 --> 59:59.156
Oh, this is terrible.

59:59.320 --> 01:00:03.154
We're behaving just like
two people in love.

01:00:04.280 --> 01:00:07.477
Which means this argument was
the final straw. This has to be the end.

01:00:07.800 --> 01:00:08.949
Or just the beginning.

01:00:09.120 --> 01:00:14.513
Holy cow. This argument has made me
realize that I must really care about you.

01:00:14.680 --> 01:00:17.911
I'm finally ready
to get to know you better.

01:00:18.560 --> 01:00:20.118
How much better?

01:00:20.760 --> 01:00:22.478
All the way better.

01:00:23.480 --> 01:00:24.469
Really?

01:00:24.640 --> 01:00:27.950
I'm sorry I have to say this,
Barbara, but...

01:00:28.680 --> 01:00:30.796
...I love you.

01:00:31.880 --> 01:00:37.034
Well, I don't have any rules
against men falling in love.

01:00:37.200 --> 01:00:40.078
So I can make love to you?

01:00:40.240 --> 01:00:44.199
Heartfelt, passionate,
worshipping, adoring love...

01:00:44.360 --> 01:00:47.670
...and you could still have
meaningless sex with me, right?

01:00:48.440 --> 01:00:50.078
Yes.

01:00:50.680 --> 01:00:53.194
So are we still on
for tomorrow night?

01:00:53.760 --> 01:00:55.671
Yes.

01:00:55.840 --> 01:00:58.274
Oh, yes.

01:01:00.920 --> 01:01:03.957
That pink book is ruining my life.

01:01:04.120 --> 01:01:06.554
Woman acts as if she has
a mind of her own.

01:01:06.760 --> 01:01:08.671
She refuses my advances.

01:01:08.880 --> 01:01:11.599
This goes to the sanctity
of a man's most fundamental right.

01:01:11.800 --> 01:01:13.597
All our wives are giving us trouble.

01:01:13.800 --> 01:01:17.554
I'm not talking about my wife.
I'm talking about my mistress.

01:01:17.760 --> 01:01:20.354
I want that Vikki Hiller fired!

01:01:20.720 --> 01:01:24.872
But you can't fire her now, T.B.

01:01:25.200 --> 01:01:27.270
How would it look?

